{"lemma":"إِبْهامٌ","slug":"إِبْهامٌ","root":"ب.ه.م","root_slug":"ب-ه-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ه-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3459"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of أَبْهَمَ (ʔabhama, “to make obscure”) (form IV)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"obscurity, vagueness, ambiguity"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thumb"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"big toe"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of أَبْهَمَ (ʔabhama, “to make obscure”) from ب ه م (b h m).\n\nWith labial assimilation – not found in بَنَان (banān, “fingers”) – related to Akkadian 𒋗𒅆 (ubānum, “finger”), Eblaite 𒁀𒂍𒈝 (ba-ʾà-núm /⁠bahānum⁠/), Hebrew בֹּהֶן (bṓhen, “thumb”), Mehri hābḗn (“thumb”), Harsusi ḥābēn."},"ipa":["/ib.haːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3459","headword_ar":"اـِبْهَامٌ","root":"bhm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thumb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great toe;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatest"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iSobaE","text_ar":"اـِصْبَع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, T, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is next to the forefinger, having two joints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because it closes upon [the palm of] the hand, as a cover; (T, TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatest of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbiE","text_ar":"اَصَابِع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the foot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) of the fem. gender, (S, Msb,) accord. to common repute; (Msb;) and sometimes masc.: (Lh, M, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahiymN","text_ar":"بَهِيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; mentioned by Az in the T, and by others; but Az adds that one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaAmN","text_ar":"بِهَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbhAm","text_ar":"ابهام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAhiymu","text_ar":"اَبَاهِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAhimu","text_ar":"اَبَاهِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which latter is used by poetic license for the former, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibohaAmaAtN","text_ar":"اـِبْهَامَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoSaru mino A_ibohaAmi AlD~ab~i","text_ar":"اَقْصَرُ مِنْ اـِبْهَامِ الضَّبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shorter than the great toe of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lizard called"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn AbhAm","text_ar":"من ابهام"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaTaApi","text_ar":"القَطَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than the back toe of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird called"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTAp","text_ar":"قطاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn AbhAm AlHubaAraY","text_ar":"من ابهام الحُبَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than the back toe of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bird called"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HbArY","text_ar":"حبارى"},{"kind":"text","text":"], are proverbs of the Arabs. (Har p. 335.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","T","S","M","K","Msb","Lh","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}